import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['time'] = pd.to_datetime(data['time'], errors='ignore')
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    plt.plot(data['time'], data['count'])
    plt.xlabel('Time')
    plt.ylabel('Count')
    plt.title('What is the overall trend of count over time?')
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    plt.hist(data['count'], bins='auto')
    plt.xlabel('Count')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    ax = plt.gca()
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        ax.xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.title('What is the distribution of count?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    
    data['time'] = pd.to_datetime(data['time'], errors='ignore')
    data['hour'] = data['time'].dt.hour
    avg_count_per_hour = data.groupby('hour')['count'].mean()
    
    ax = avg_count_per_hour.plot(kind='bar')
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        ax.xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.title("What is the average count per hour?", wrap=True)
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    data['time'] = pd.to_datetime(data['time'], errors='ignore')
    data['day_of_week'] = data['time'].dt.day_name()
    box_plot = data.boxplot(column='count', by='day_of_week', rot=45)
    plt.title('What is the distribution of count by day of the week?')
    plt.suptitle('')
    plt.xlabel('Day of the Week')
    plt.ylabel('Count')
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        box_plot.xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()
